-- Banks May Swap Premafin Debt Into Equity, Il Messaggero Says
-- B y   S o n i a   S i r l e t t i
-- 2012-01-03T09:07:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-03/banks-may-swap-premafin-debt-into-equity-il-messaggero-says.html
Mediobanca SpA (MB)  and  UniCredit SpA (UCG)  may
convert loans given to  Premafin Finanziaria SpA (PF)  into equity as
part of a plan to boost the capital of the holding company
controlling  Fondiaria-SAI SpA (FSA) , newspaper  Il Messaggero  said,
without saying where it got the information.  Separately, executives of  Unipol Gruppo Finanziario SpA (UNI)  and
Premafin will meet in Milan today to discuss a potential merger
with Fondiaria, the daily newspaper reported.  Premafin, Unipol and Fondiaria yesterday rose in Milan
trading on speculation the three companies may merge.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sonia Sirletti in Milan at 
 ssirletti@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at   fconnelly@bloomberg.net  